  "body": "\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`):\r\n1.6.4 for both server and client\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: GKE and On premise\r\n- **OS** (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Debian Jessie and Ubuntu 16.04\r\n- **Kernel** (e.g. `uname -a`): 4.4.0-78 (ubuntu)\r\n- **Install tools**: Managed service for GKE, Ansible for on premise\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen I define a resource quota limit with GPU resources in it to limit the number of GPU allocated to a namespace as  \r\n\r\n```apiVersion: v1\r\nkind: ResourceQuota\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: quota\r\n  namespace: test\r\nspec:\r\n  hard:\r\n    requests.cpu: \"12\"\r\n    requests.memory: 8Gi\r\n    requests.alpha.kubernetes.io/nvidia-gpu: \"1\"\r\n    limits.cpu: \"12\"\r\n    limits.memory: 8Gi\r\n    limits.alpha.kubernetes.io/nvidia-gpu: \"1\"\r\n    configmaps: \"100\"\r\n    services: \"100\"\r\n    secrets: \"100\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nIt creates the `quota` object without any warning. But when I try to run any deployment in that namespace, I get the error as\r\n `Warning   FailedCreate   replicaset-controller   Error creating: pods \"tensorflow-3620546736-\" is forbidden: status unknown for quota: quota`. \r\nThis error goes away if I remove the GPU from resource quota. Also looking at the [docs](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/policy/resource-quotas/) it seems GPU is not supported for quota. \r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nI expect that in the above quota case, user will be able to run workload in `test` namespace with 1 GPU at max.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\nApply the above quota to a namespace and try to deploy any deployment with or without GPU, you will see the error. \r\n\r\n\r\n",
